I am incredibly sorry for your loss Lana Tresidder and I don't mean offence by what I am about to say, but until you lose a child this way you could not understand the emotional impact it has on a family.  Every family who has a missing loved one reacts differently, the pain and anguish you live with every single day is like a nightmare you never wake up from. Your head is filled with thousands of unanswered questions, you are constantly questioning yourself and others, there is absolutely no end to the constant pain you go through as there seems no end in sight of any answers, some days you lose all hope as it doesn't seem like you are ever going to find your missing loved one, you have a constant ache in your chest, the stress and strain can take a massive toll on your health, your marriage, your friendships, your mental health, your trust of other people diminishes rapidly, you are constantly scanning the people around you wondering if they know something, ANYTHING to find your loved one, there is never a healing process as you have no body to bury so every day it is a battle.... This is just a slight insight into what a family member goes through every day with a missing loved one. No one has a right to judge what a family does unless they have gone thrpugh exactly what this family have gone through.... I should know, my family have been waiting 45 years to have my sister come home, I have watch my dad pass away through a broken heart, my brother buries his head in the sand as he struggles to cope with the loss of my sister and my mum struggles each and every day not knowing what happened to her girl. I deal with families of missing loved ones every day, each family different. Some want to be a part of media coverage others are too emotionally drained to continue...
